<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="1464" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1464">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/180.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-02">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 2, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>German Embassy reports authorities Guadalajara levying extraordinary
                            taxes discriminatory as against Germans and other foreigners as compared
                            with Mexicans.</p>
                        <p>Department had understood from Carothers that collection this
                            extraordinary tax had been suspended.</p>
                        <p>Report facts and if attempt is being made to collect tax discriminatory
                            as against foreigners make urgent protest on this ground.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>